Trần Thị Anh Thư is an Intern AI/ML/Network Security Engineer with zero years of commercial experience, focusing on academic and project-based applications. Their core expertise spans Machine Learning architectures including Feed Forward Neural Networks, Recurrent Neural Networks, KNN, Random Forest, XGBoost, and Ensemble Learning Models. They have applied advanced techniques such as Data Exploration, Data Analysis, Statistical Analysis, Visualization, Feature Engineering, Feature Evaluation, and Overfitting Prevention in predictive modeling projects. Additionally, they possess strong capabilities in Network Security, specifically DDoS Attack Prevention using Software-Defined Networking (SDN), Network Management, and Traffic Anomaly detection, complemented by foundational knowledge in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Prompt Engineering.
Technically, Trần Thị Anh Thư is proficient in Python and SQL. They have practical experience with AWS cloud services and a robust set of tools and platforms including Ubuntu, Mininet, iperf, Kali Linux, Windows Server Update Services (WSUS), Active Directory, and GitHub for collaborative development and version control. Their academic background in Computer Networks and Data Communication provides a solid understanding of network infrastructure, topology design, routers, and switches, further demonstrated through projects involving centralized update management and secure network configurations.